physical_examinations.relevant_findings: Ultrasonographic examination showed a single intrauterine gestational sac containing a normal-appearing fetus with a normal heart rate; placenta was posterior, and nuchal translucency was normal (<3 mm). Urinalysis showed 3 to 5 white cells per high-power field; urine culture grew moderate mixed bacteria and rare (100 to <1000) group B streptococci.
Pelvic examination was normal; Papanicolaou smear revealed yeast. White-cell count was 15,200 per cubic millimeter, remainder of the complete blood count was normal.
Ultrasonographic examination showed an active fetus with normal fetal and placental anatomy; biometric assessment consistent with a gestation of 19.0 weeks.
Diagnosis of costochondritis made; acetaminophen prescribed.
physical_examinations.changes_over_time: Symptom of pelvic cramping and pain resolved without treatment.

physical_examinations.vital_signs: White-cell count: 12,800 per cubic millimeter; platelet count: 370,000 per cubic millimeter; hematocrit: 34.8%; hemoglobin: 11.7 g per deciliter.
physical_examinations.relevant_findings: Normal fetal activity noted; glucose-tolerance test results were normal.
Fetal growth and activity appropriate for gestational dates; rash developed on left inner thigh which resolved within 10 days.
physical_examinations.changes_over_time: A second similar lesion on the right arm also resolved spontaneously.

physical_examinations.relevant_findings: Weight gain of 8.62 kg in pregnancy; fundal height normal at 37 weeks' gestation; estimated fetal weight 3400 g (45th percentile); fetal heart rate and amniotic fluid volume normal.

Physical examination showed normal findings, except for a fully dilated cervix; sterile vaginal examination revealed intact and bulging amniotic sac; external fetal monitor did not detect fetal heartbeat.
physical_examinations.changes_over_time: Fetal movements ceased approximately 7 hours before delivery; fetal death confirmed by ultrasonographic examination.
